---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'Best Self-Propelled Petrol Lawn Mowers UK 2026';
const description = 'Self-propelled petrol mowers for UK lawns. We cover the best models for medium to large gardens, chosen from specs and verified owner reviews.';
const path = '/petrol-lawn-mowers/self-propelled/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Petrol lawn mowers', url: '/petrol-lawn-mowers/' },
  { name: 'Self-propelled', url: path },
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is a self-propelled petrol mower worth the extra cost?',
    a: 'If your lawn is over 300 m² or has any slope at all, yes. Pushing a 25-30 kg petrol mower uphill every week gets old fast. Self-propelled adds £50-£150 to the price and saves your knees.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Front-wheel or rear-wheel drive - which is better?',
    a: 'Rear-wheel drive gives better traction on slopes and damp grass. Front-wheel drive is easier to turn at the end of each stripe. For most UK gardens, rear-wheel is the better choice.',
  },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
].filter(Boolean);
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} schema={schema}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Petrol Guide · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">Best Self-Propelled Petrol Mowers UK 2026</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        If you've got a big garden and you're sick of pushing, a self-propelled petrol mower does the hard work for you. We've compared the best options from Mountfield, Honda and Cobra against specs and verified owner reviews.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>Why self-propelled matters</h2>
      <p>
        A self-propelled mower drives its own wheels - you just steer. On a flat 200 m² lawn that's a nice-to-have. On a sloped 600 m² garden, it's the difference between enjoying the mow and dreading it. Most use a rear-wheel drive system powered off the engine via a belt.
      </p>

      <h2>Three self-propelled petrol mowers we recommend</h2>

      <h3>1. Mountfield SP46 Elite (£449)</h3>
      <p>
        The workhorse. Mountfield's 46 cm steel deck, Honda GCVx170 engine, variable-speed rear drive and a 60 L grass box. This is the mower UK garden centres sell more of than anything else, and for good reason - it just works, year after year. <a href="/reviews/mountfield-sp46/" class="text-grass-700 underline">Read our Mountfield SP46 review</a> <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?k=mountfield+sp46+lawn+mower&amp;tag=thebestmowers-21" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="text-grass-700 underline whitespace-nowrap">Check price &rarr;</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Honda HRX 476 VK (£899)</h3>
      <p>
        The premium pick. Honda's own GCVx200 engine, Versamow selective mulching, Roto-Stop blade brake (engine keeps running when you let go), and a build quality that'll outlast most gardens. Expensive, but you're buying a mower for 15+ years. <a href="/reviews/honda-hrx-476-vk/" class="text-grass-700 underline">Read our Honda HRX review</a> <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?k=honda+hrx+476+vk+lawn+mower&amp;tag=thebestmowers-21" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="text-grass-700 underline whitespace-nowrap">Check price &rarr;</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Cobra MX46SPB (£349)</h3>
      <p>
        The budget self-propelled option. Cobra's Briggs &amp; Stratton-powered 46 cm mower does everything the Mountfield does at £100 less. Build quality isn't quite as polished, but the engine and drive system are solid. <a href="/reviews/cobra-mx46spb/" class="text-grass-700 underline">Read our Cobra review</a> <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/s?k=cobra+mx46spb+lawn+mower&amp;tag=thebestmowers-21" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="text-grass-700 underline whitespace-nowrap">Check price &rarr;</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Self-propelled vs push - the honest trade-off</h2>
      <p>
        Self-propelled costs more, weighs slightly more (the drive mechanism adds 2-3 kg), and has one more thing that can break. But on any lawn over 300 m² or with a slope, you'll be glad you paid the extra. Push mowers are best kept for small, flat gardens.
      </p>
    </div>

    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
